## Quote Collection

**On Order:**
> "People say they want freedom. But what they really want is safety. Security. The certainty that tomorrow will be like today. I give them that. I give them peace."

**On the Clone Program:**
> "Every clone is an upgrade. We keep the useful parts—the knowledge, the relationships, the position—and remove the weakness. The doubt. The disloyalty. It's not murder. It's evolution."

**On Opposition:**
> "They call me a fascist. A tyrant. As if those words mean anything anymore. I'm a pragmatist. I see a problem. I solve it. If that makes me a villain in their eyes, so be it. History will vindicate me."

**On Ahdia:**
> "The Bacchus girl thinks she's a hero because she's powerful. But power without vision is just chaos. I'll give her a choice: Use that power for something greater, or watch me build my better world over her corpse."

**If Clone Questioning:**
> "Sometimes I wonder if the real Harding Kain would have gone this far. Then I remember: I *am* Harding Kain. The doubts are just programming errors. Ghosts of the original's weakness. I will not inherit his failures."

**Final Confrontation:**
> "You've won nothing. Even if you stop me, do you think I'm the only one? We're everywhere now. In every precinct, every courthouse, every boardroom. The transformation has already begun. You can't stop an idea whose time has come."

**On Humanity:**
> "Humanity is a rough draft. I'm simply providing the edits."

